# Code Using Linked-List cycle Method
```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int findDuplicate(vector<int>& nums) {
        int slow = nums[0];
        int fast = nums[0];

        // Phase 1: Detect the cycle
        do {
            slow = nums[slow];
            fast = nums[nums[fast]];
        } while (slow != fast);

        // Phase 2: Find the entrance to the cycle
        slow = nums[0];
        while (slow != fast) {
            slow = nums[slow];
            fast = nums[fast];
        }

        return slow; // or fast, as they both point to the entrance of the cycle
    }
};

```
