# Intuition
SWAP SORT

# Approach
Here one element is extra which is repeated.
We have to place all the element at the index where the element has the right place.
What is the right place?
EX : [2,1,3,4,2]
Right place : [1,2,3,4,2]
Each element should present at the index i-1.
1 at index 0.
2 at index 1.
....
After we get each element at right place.We have to traverse the array and chack which element is not present at their right place.
Which is our ans.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    // FOR SWAPPING
    void swap(vector<int>&nums,int i,int j){
        int d=nums[i];
        nums[i]=nums[j];
        nums[j]=d;
    }


    int findDuplicate(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size(),i=0;
        // PLACING THE ELEMENT AT THE RIGHT PLACE.
        while(i<n){
            if(nums[i]!=nums[nums[i]-1]){
                swap(nums,i,nums[i]-1);
            }
            else{
                i++;
            }
        }
        int d=-1;

        // CHECKING THE ELEMENT PRESENT AT THEIR RIGHT PLACE OR NOT.
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]!=(i+1)){
                return nums[i];
            }
        }
        return d;
    }
};
```

