class Solution {
    /**
     * First approac is very simple, since we know that there must be at least one 
     *  duplicate number and the largest number is n, we create an array of n elements
     *  and check each element after we seen it in the nums array.
     *  
     *  If at one point we see an element that is already checked in the array, we found
     *  the duplicate number
     *
     *  Time complexity: O(N)
     *  Space complexity: O(N)
     *   public int findDuplicate(int[] nums) {
     *       boolean[] check = new boolean[nums.length];
     *       for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
     *           if (check[nums[i]]) return nums[i];
     *
     *           check[nums[i]] = true;
     *       }
     *
     *       return 0;
     *   }
     ***/

    /**
     * The second approach use a fast and slow pointers approach to find the starting
     * point of a cycle in a linked list.
     *
     * The fast pointer will always step over 2 nodes, the slow pointer will always step over 1 node
     * Since there is a cycle in the list, the 2 pointers will eventually meet each other.
     *
     * After that we just bring one pointer back to the start, and then make them both step over 1
     * node at a time, when they meet each other, we have found the start of the cycle.
     *
     * For more detailed explanation: Please see the Solution section.
     * Time complexity: O(N)
     * Space complexity: O(1)
     */
    public int findDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        int fastPointer = 0, slowPointer = 0;

		// Phase 1: Try to make them meet each other
        do 
        {
            fastPointer = nums[nums[fastPointer]];
            slowPointer = nums[slowPointer];
        }
        while (fastPointer != slowPointer);

		// Phase 2: Bring the slow pointer to the start and make them move over 1 by 1
        slowPointer = 0;
        while (slowPointer != fastPointer) {
            slowPointer = nums[slowPointer];
            fastPointer = nums[fastPointer];
        }

        return slowPointer;
    }
}
