# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We just have to go through array from left to right calculating the right side sum and left side sum. 
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Since we are asked to get left most index, we can start from index = 0 as potential pivot. Left sum = 0, right sum = (sum of all elements starting from index 1)(because 0 is our pivot). 

Than we just go through our array adding to left sum i'th(previous potential pivot) index and substructing from right sum (i+1)'th(new potential pivot) and check if they satisfie the conditions(leftSum == rightSum)
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Java code
```
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {
        int rightSum = 0, leftSum = 0;
        for (var i = 1; i < nums.length; ++i) {
            rightSum += nums[i];
        }

        for (var i = 0; i < nums.length; ++i) {
            if (rightSum == leftSum) {
                return i;
            }
            leftSum += nums[i];
            if (i + 1 < nums.length) {
                rightSum -= nums[i+1];
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```
