# Intuition
We need to compare left and right sum.

# Approach
First we calculate the sum of all elements in the array. Then we traverse the array and calculate the left sum side by side. At each element, we compare the left sum (subtracting the element at the current index so that we get the potential pivot element) with the right sum (total-left). If they are equal return the index.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
