The left sum of `nums[i]` is so-called the prefix sum.
```
Total sum = prefix sum + nums[i] + right sum.
```

Calculating total sum in advance gives right sum while calculating the prefix sum.

Whenever the prefix sum equals to the right sum, we find the pivot index.

```
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {
        int sum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            sum += num;
        }

        int prefixSum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if (prefixSum == sum - prefixSum - nums[i]) {
                return i;
            }
            prefixSum += nums[i];
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

