# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
First Since we have to find left and right sum at each index i where arr[i] will be excluded
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. first, find total sum. 
2. next, we find left Sum by adding arr[i] at each iteration.
3. so right sum will be total - nums[i] - leftSum
4. at each iteration checkl whenever a condition leftSum == rightSum satisfies, return i
5. otherwise return -1

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] arr) {
        int leftSum = 0, rightSum = 0, sum = 0;
        for( int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++ ){
            sum += arr[i];
        }
        for( int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++ ){
            rightSum = sum - arr[i] - leftSum;
            if (leftSum == rightSum)
                return i;
            leftSum += arr[i];
        }
        return -1;
    }

}
```

