solutions.content:
We have to compare the forward sum with the backward sum, while not including the pivot number for each.

For this, we can initialize `backwardSum` as the total sum and `forwardSum` as 0. 

After, we can subtract the pivot number from `backwardSum` at each step. 
Then, we can check if the `forwardSum` and `backwardSum` are equal, as they both do not include the pivot number now. 
Lastly, we can add the pivot number to `forwardSum` and move a step.

<br>

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/bc1ce5d6-c4d7-4358-8983-a8f6fb80eec1_1662448814.008453.png)

<br>

You can find the sample code below.

```
int pivotIndex(vector<int>& nums) {
	  // Calculate the total value
      int backwardSum = accumulate(nums.begin(), nums.end(), 0);

      int forwardSum = 0;
      for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i) {
          backwardSum -= nums[i];
          if (forwardSum == backwardSum) return i;
          forwardSum += nums[i];
      }

      return -1;
}
```

